import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='Date', y='CO2', data=data, label='CO2 levels')
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 levels over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='CO2', bins=30, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['CO2'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['CO2'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Levels')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 levels?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Date'])]

    max_co2 = data['CO2'].max()
    max_co2_date = data.loc[data['CO2'] == max_co2, 'Date'].iloc[0]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='Date', y='CO2', data=data)
    plt.axhline(y=max_co2, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest CO2: {max_co2:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the highest CO2 level recorded?', wrap=True)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
